definition.value: An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups and protonation of the amino group of validamine 7-phosphate; major species at pH 7.3.
An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups and protonation of the amino group of validoxylamine A 7'-phosphate; major species at pH 7.3.
An organic cation resulting from the protonation of the amino group of validoxylamine A; major species at pH 7.3.
A tetrol consisting of pentane with four hydroxy substituents placed at positions 1, 2, 4 and 5.
A hydroxyalkyl phosphate obtained by monophosphorylation of ethylene glycol.
A galactosylglycerol in which an alpha-D-galactosyl residue is attartched to position 2 of glycerol via a glycosidic bond.
An amino trisaccharide which has an N-acetyl-D-glucosamine unit at the reducing end with an alpha-L-colitosyl-(1->2)-beta-D-galactosyl group attached at the 3-position.
An alicyclic compound that is cyclopentene substituted at positions 1 and 3 by hydroxy and methyl groups respectively.
A pyrimidine 2'-deoxyribonucleoside 5'-monophosphate having beta-D-glucopyranosyloxymethyluracil (base J) as the nucleobase
A tetrol consisting of 1-iminohexane with four hydroxy substituents placed at positions 2, 3, 4 and 5.
A pyrimidine 2'-deoxyribonucleoside having beta-D-glucopyranosyloxymethyluracil (base J) as the nucleobase.
The furanose form of any pentose.
A 3-sn-phosphatidyl-L-serine(1-) that is the conjugate base of 1,2-dihexadecanoyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-L-serine; major species at pH 7.3.
A nucleoside residue derived from (beta-D-glucopyranosyloxymethyl)deoxyuridine.
A dicarboxylic acid that is malonic acid in which both methylene hydrogens have been replaced by methyl groups.
An alkadiene that is octane with the two double bonds located at positions 2 and 6.
A dichloromuconic acid in which the two chloro groups are placed at positions 2 and 3.
A triol consisting of 1-iminobutane with three hydroxy substituents placed at positions 2, 3 and 4.
A member of the class of cyclohexenones that is cyclohex-2-en-1-one substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 4, 5 and 6, and by a hydroxymethyl group at position 3 (the 4R,5S,6R-diastereomer).
An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of valienone 7-phosphate; major species at pH 7.3.
